		   <tr><td valign="top" class="mform" ><span class="fs8"><span class="notbold">By: </span><a href="/db/poster.html?user=238703"><span class="">GambitTheGreatt</span></a><b><span class=""></span></b><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />154 posts
		   <br /><span class="nobr"><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Default  </span><br />
<br/><a href="/db/classes.html?class=3;mid=106799628427064;page=1;howmany=50#106799628427064"><img alt="" title="Use this to create a link to this post" src="/shared/garrowrt.png" border="0" height="9" width="11" /> Link to this post</a>

<br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1" alt=""/></span></td>
<td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%">
<p>ok, first off, please dont flame me, this is strictly MY OPINION. <br /> <br />Ok, so, your all probly wondering &quot;why would someone dislike monks?&quot; and i can answer that simply by saying POSERS. I dont have a problem with any class except the monks, i mean, they think they're tanks, but i STRONGLY disagree. A tank must have a bunch of HP in order to stand strong and defend your group in battle. Monks really dont have that much HP, and yes, they do deal damage pretty nicely, but really, what is the point of a tank if he cant stay alive long enough to deal that damage. I also dont like monks because they never give warriors NEARLY enough respect, they dont know really how hard our job is. If we fail to taunt, BAM, groups dead. If we move just 2 feet and move the mob BAM, theres an instant add and then, BAM, groups dead. I can see monks as being secondary tanks, but NEVER should they be the primary tank. Theres a reason why monks have FD, and thats because they cant take mobs directly, so, they made FD to make it so they die less often because when they FD the agro is gone. Im sorry if i make any of you monks angry, but this is how i feel, and to those of you that realize that your not supposed to be a main tank, thank you, and please keep doing your job well. I do realize that monks are important in a group but... <br /> <br />Ok, well, like i said, sorry i anger anyone, these are just my feeling, and also, please respond to this with your feeling about monk/warrior relationships. <br /> <br />Thank you! <br /> <br /></p>
<br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />~~~~~~~~~Gambit~~~~~~~~~~ <br />    ~~Bertoxx Server~~ <br />       ~~Semi retired 61 warrior =(~~ <br /> <br /> <br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=515555" title="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=515555" target="akztarg">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_pr...?num=515555</a></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td class="fs8"></td><td align="right" class="fs8" >66 replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table>
