<td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p>Ok first off buddy you need to stop with the GENERALIZATIONS.  Exactly what gave you the idea that ALL monks think they are tanks?  My main is a SK and out of all the monks I've grouped with they never tell my group &quot;I am the main tank here and I hate all warriors!&quot;  I play a 30 Monk and I certainly don't like having aggro nor do I claim to be a tank.  I certainly can take aggro from a warrior but do I want aggro? No.  And IMO a TANK is a class that has alot of hit points, AC, and someone that can peel a mob off anyone in a instant.  Does a monk meet those requirements?  No.  And I think a Monk is better off grouping with a SK or Pally since those 2 classes can take and hold aggro better than most warriors.  Why do I say this?  I've seen it done many times and I've done it many times myself.  In your next post please try to not generalize so much.</p>
