<td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%">
<p>This entire thread is kind of silly. <br /> <br />There arent a lot of Monks running around these days anyway.  We arent essential to any group I know of.  No matter what aspect of being a Monk you mention some other class can probably handle it better.  But overall playing a Monk is fun.  Those who know me are happy to have me in their groups.  With the right support we Monks are DPS.  At level 57 without an epic Ill steal agro from a epic rogue every time, which is good as they have glass jaws.  I solo a lot in POJ and anyone wanting to join me is quickly invited. <br /> <br />Remember everything is relative.  If Im in a place where I can solo consistently a Tank can tank only if he can steal the agro.  If he can steal it then good for him, and me.  If Im in a raid, or high risk Zone, Ill pull out my lower damage weapons, and FD if necessary to let that tank keep agro. <br /> <br />Tanks are not designed to be killers, but survivors.  They walk up to mobs that have 20 times their hit points and die slow enough that the clerics can keep them alive in a raid.  Monks are designed to be killers in any given fight my tank friend and I compare damage and I sometimes out damage him by 3 to 1, but as rogues are to Monks so Monks are to Tanks, by comparison we do have glass jaws. <br /> <br />Then theres equipment, buffs, and dont forget tribute (if KEI is Crack, tribute is Steroids) can all effect who takes the lead in any given fight. <br /></p>
