<td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p>Well, I'm not going to go so far as to say that monks are tanks, but whether or not they CAN tank depends a LOT on gear. My level 57 monk was tanking the golem type mobs at West wall camp in PoV, and they con red to him. let me clarify by saying he was not Supposed to be the tank, but the tank LD, and we got bored waiting for him to return so I pulled and tanked a few. <br /> <br />I don't have any ultra special gear, its all bazaar purchased stuff. Admittedly some of the better bazaar purchased stuff, but still, hes no PoTime equipped Monk, and with shammy and cleric buffs he ends up with over 1200ac and 5k+ hp. <br /> <br />Honestly, the biggest problem I had attempting to tank, was not the ability to take hits, but the inability to taunt. Monk aggro generation really is as poor or worse than warriors were prior to the introduction of the bellow, berate. incite line of effects. I was using my highest aggro weapons (Copper hammer of striking and adamantite club), and still lost the mob a few times when the shammy slowed. Our solution was to root the mob, then slow. By the time root broke, I had usually reestablished top spot on the hate list. <br /> <br />I might also add that I have a level 57 warrior as well, and I certainly admit freely that he outtanks the monk. But to say the monk CANNOT tank, is failing to recognize his full potential. Certainly a monk cannot tank named mobs, or raid targets, but against typical grind mobs in normal ldon, tier 1 or two PoP, and even the easier GoD zones, a decently equipped monk does just fine, assuming the rest of the group is up to the task.</p>
