<p>/totally agree with Emmo. <br /> <br />I'm a level 54 monk and am very twinked.  My AC is around 1166 and my buffed hit points around 4600-4800.  I love pulling and my dps which gives me a great sense of contribution to the group, but if there is no assigned main tank due to the group makeup (i.e., chanter, wizard, cleric, ranger, shammy and me), then I do pretty well as a tank.  I have tanked PoI, GE, Natimbi, etc. with no problem at all especially with holding aggro, which I usually steal from any class but rogue anyways.  However, believe me, I would much rather assist a real tank than be one.  My dps goes way up when I'm not getting slammed and stunned all the time.  I love monks, I love their safe fall, their FD, the dps, our ability to mend.... <br /> <br />~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~ <br />Sharthis Razorspine <br />Disciple of the 54th Teaching <br />Journeyman Chef <br />Loyal Follower of Cazic-Thule <br />Torv Server</p>
