<p><div class="msgquote"><div class="msgquotesrc">Quote:</div><div class="msgqorig">Ok, so, your all probly wondering &quot;why would someone dislike monks?&quot; and i can answer that simply by saying POSERS. I dont have a problem with any class except the monks, i mean, they think they're tanks, but i STRONGLY disagree. A tank must have a bunch of HP in order to stand strong and defend your group in battle. Monks really dont have that much HP, and yes, they do deal damage pretty nicely, but really, what is the point of a tank if he cant stay alive long enough to deal that damage.</div></div> I see my Monk as a Puller (and a damn good one) and as DPS. I leave the tanking to the Tanks. If a mob needs to be peeled of a healer or caster, then I'm happy to do so and if needed I'll happily step up and &quot;tank&quot;, but I don't expect to &quot;be the Main Tnak&quot; when i join a group, with my Monk.<div class="msgquote"><div class="msgquotesrc">Quote:</div><div class="msgqorig">I also dont like monks because they never give warriors NEARLY enough respect, they dont know really how hard our job is. If we fail to taunt, BAM, groups dead. If we move just 2 feet and move the mob BAM, theres an instant add and then, BAM, groups dead.</div></div> You need to find better groups, if they die that quickly.<div class="msgquote"><div class="msgquotesrc">Quote:</div><div class="msgqorig">I can see monks as being secondary tanks, but NEVER should they be the primary tank. Theres a reason why monks have FD, and thats because they cant take mobs directly, so, they made FD to make it so they die less often because when they FD the agro is gone.</div></div> I find turning off /auto attack for a few seconds works a treat and normally gives agro back to the MT, if I should happen to gain agro from him. Doesn't happen very often though, since I'm usually off getting our next mob to kill.<div class="msgquote"><div class="msgquotesrc">Quote:</div><div class="msgqorig">Im sorry if i make 