<td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%">
<p>In the beginning there was a monk.  He/she was alone, but that was ok.  He/she could deliver much damage and get things done.  But the cost was high, he/she spent too much time resting.   <br /> <br />So the monk got a pet. This pet was called 'cleric'.  They were together and it was  ok.  After a while the cleric-pet got overworked from constantly healing the monk.   <br /> <br />So the cleric-pet got a pet.  It was called 'warrior' and did not require as much tending as the monk.  Now the three were together, and it was ok.  The monk went about merrily doing damage, not taking much in turn.  The cleric was happy not having to work so hard.  The warrior was, well a warrior.   <br /> <br />Well this led to that, the warrior decided the monk could use some help with damage (so the warrior would finish his job quicker).  They added a few more and before you know it, there were 6, and they all did their part, some jobs EVEN overlapped (imagine that?).  Now they could do even BIGGER things together. <br /> <br />Monks can tank when they have to, but why should they if they have a pet or two? <br /> <br /> <br /> <br /></p>
