<td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p>Whether a monk can tank, really depends on what you mean by &quot;tank&quot;. NO, a monk will not be tanking the hardest mob in cutting edge encounters, but a monk can certainly pass as a grind group tank, if equipped well. Just last night, I had a monk tanking mobs in a PG group trial (fear). <br /> <br />I've also been in on AoW kills, where a monk tanked statue, while we waited on the plate tank to arrive for the actual AoW kill.  <br /> <br />No, a monk isn't going to tank Queen Gelagua in riftseekers, but he CAN tank the regular one group mobs, providing his gear is good. <br /> <br />BTW, I cannot believe this old thread got revived again.</p>
