<td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p>In response to the original poster... <br /> <br />Monks can't be tanks because they don't have the AC, you say? <br /> <br />That is the silliest thing I've heard in a long time. <br /> <br />The biggest reason I hated being asked to tank with my monk, even though she had more than enough AC and HP was because to tank, really tank, requires one very important skill that monks simply do not posess...TAUNT. <br /> <br />Tanking is about keeping a mobs attention, monks have no means of ensuring that they do so. All the HP in the world isn't going to get the attention of the mob that the shaman just debuffed and slowed until you've been beating on it a good long while.</p>
